==English==

===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} {{term|almande}}, from Romanic *{{term||amendla}} (with ''-l-'' in French and Spanish, probably by confusion with similar Arabic words), from {{L.}} {{term|amygdala}}, from {{AGr.}} {{term|ἀμυγδάλη|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* (''UK'') {{IPA|/ˈɑːmənd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-almond.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{countable}} A type of [[tree]] [[nut]].
# {{countable}} A small [[deciduous]] tree, ''Prunus dulcis'', that produces almonds.
# {{context|countable|uncountable}} The [[colour]] of the [[kernel]] of an almond without its [[shell]] and thin [[seed coat]], a [[creamy]] off-[[white]] colour.

